気道基底細胞形態異常

any structural anomaly of a long-lived multipotent stem cell of the pseudostratified airway epithelium which is restricted to the tracheal epithelium in mice; airway BCs have been shown to be capable of self renewal, give rise to secretory (Clara) cells and ciliated cells, and play important roles both in epithelial homeostasis and in pathological airway remodeling
気道基底細胞分化異常

abnormal or arrest of differentiation of the long-lived multipotent stem cell population of the pseudostratified airway epithelium; changes in the lineage choice of BCs or their undifferentiated daughters might contribute to the mucous cell hyperplasia, metaplasia or squamous metaplasia seen in many respiratory disorders
気道基底細胞の過形成
increased number of the long-lived multipotent stem cells of the pseudostratified airway epithelium
ライヘルト膜の欠如

absence of the extraembryonic basement membrane that forms on the inner surface of the trophectoderm during placenta morphogenesis and is secreted by the distal endoderm; normally required for the maternofetal exchange of nutrients and important for postgastrulation development
体重増加感受性異常
anomaly in body weight over time when compared to the average increase in weight on the same diet, with equal energy (calorie) intake

definition.value: These terms should be used when there is some external intervention that is expected to alter the weight of both the experimental and control groups or for alterantions in age-related changes in body weight.

value.value: 体重減少感受性異常
anomaly in body weight over time when compared to the average decrease in weight in response to dietary modification, fasting or caloric restriction
原始卵胞の数の異常
abnormal numbers of the ovarian follicle that is indiscernible to the naked eye and develops into to primary, secondary, and finally mature vesicular follicles
原始卵胞の数の増加
greater than normal numbers of the ovarian follicle that is indiscernible to the naked eye and develops into to primary, secondary, and finally mature vesicular follicles
原始卵胞の数の減少
fewer than normal numbers of the ovarian follicle that is indiscernible to the naked eye and develops into to primary, secondary, and finally mature vesicular follicles
原始卵胞の欠如
absence of the ovarian follicle that is indiscernible to the naked eye and develops into to primary, secondary, and finally mature vesicular follicles
一次卵胞の数の異常
abnormal numbers of the ovarian follicle that is characterized by the presence of a single layer of granulosa cells
一次卵胞の数の増加
greater than normal numbers of the ovarian follicle that is characterized by the presence of a single layer of granulosa cells
一次卵胞の数の減少
fewer than normal numbers of the ovarian follicle that is characterized by the presence of a single layer of granulosa cells
一次卵胞の欠如
absence of the ovarian follicle that is characterized by the presence of a single layer of granulosa cells
二次卵胞の数の異常

abnormal numbers of the ovarian follicle in which the primary oocyte attains its full size and is surrounded by an extracellular glycoprotein layer (zona pellucida) that separates it from a peripheral layer of follicular cells permeated by one or more fluid-filled antra; the primary oocyte occupies the cumulus oophorus while the theca of the follicle develops into internal and external layers
二次卵胞の数の増加

greater than normal numbers of the ovarian follicle in which the primary oocyte attains its full size and is surrounded by an extracellular glycoprotein layer (zona pellucida) that separates it from a peripheral layer of follicular cells permeated by one or more fluid-filled antra; the primary oocyte occupies the cumulus oophorus while the theca of the follicle develops into internal and external layers
二次卵胞の数の減少

fewer than normal numbers of the ovarian follicle in which the primary oocyte attains its full size and is surrounded by an extracellular glycoprotein layer (zona pellucida) that separates it from a peripheral layer of follicular cells permeated by one or more fluid-filled antra; the primary oocyte occupies the cumulus oophorus while the theca of the follicle develops into internal and external layers
二次卵胞の欠如

absence of the ovarian follicle in which the primary oocyte attains its full size and is surrounded by an extracellular glycoprotein layer (zona pellucida) that separates it from a peripheral layer of follicular cells permeated by one or more fluid-filled antra; the primary oocyte occupies the cumulus oophorus while the theca of the follicle develops into internal and external layers
肺内皮細胞の生理異常
any functional anomaly of the squamous cells forming the lining of the pulmonary vasculature
肺内皮細胞の遊走異常
anomaly in the movement of endothelial cells or their precursors to the appropriate location in the pulmonary vasculature
肺内皮細胞の遊走亢進
increased or faster movement of endothelial cells or their precursors to the appropriate location in the pulmonary vasculature
肺内皮細胞の遊走低下
reduced or slower movement of endothelial cells or their precursors to the appropriate location in the pulmonary vasculature
肺内皮細胞の接着異常
altered ability of an endothelial cell in the pulmonary vasculature to adhere to another cell or to a non-cellular component of the environment
肺内皮細胞の接着亢進
increased ability of an endothelial cell in the pulmonary vasculature to adhere to another cell or to a non-cellular component of the environment
肺内皮細胞の接着低下
decreased ability of an endothelial cell in the pulmonary vasculature to adhere to another cell or to a non-cellular component of the environment
肺内皮細胞の増殖異常
altered ability of an endothelial cell in the pulmonary vasculature to undergo expansion by cell division
肺内皮細胞の増殖増加
greater ability of an endothelial cell in the pulmonary vasculature to undergo expansion by cell division
肺内皮細胞の増殖減少
reduced ability of an endothelial cell in the pulmonary vasculature to undergo expansion by cell division
肺内皮細胞のアポトーシス増加
acceleration in the timing or in the number of endothelial cells in the pulmonary vasculature undergoing programmed cell death
肺関連間充織の発生異常

abnormality in the formation of the lung tissue comprised of multiple cell types (including connective tissue, endothelial cells, lymphatics, smooth muscle cells surrounding airways and blood vessels, myofibroblasts involved in septum formation, and cartilage-forming cells in the trachea), with most cells thought to be derived from the splanchnic mesenchyme, and other cells (endothelial, smooth muscle) believed to invade the lung as it expands; lung mesenchyme is a critical determinant of the shape and size of the developing lung, the extent and patterning of epithelial branching, and the formation of the pulmonary vasculature and interstitial mesenchymal components of the adult lung
肺関連間充織の肥厚
increased thickness of the mesenchymal cell layer due to delay or failure of the mesenchymal compartment to thin down during the late stages of embryonic lung development
肺関連間充織の菲薄化
decreased thickness of the mesenchymal cell layer in the developing lung
